\N<Irime>You've probably guessed it by now, haven't you?

\N<Irime>By doing that with that guy Zuuteruka, I was able to get him
to arrange my opponents for me. To assign me opponents that
would be advantageous for me as a woman.
\N<Segi>Ms. Irime...

\N<Irime>Heh, do you despise me? Of course, under normal
circumstances, I wouldn't have wanted to do such things.

\N<Irime>But... I had no choice if I wanted to protect my family.
That was the only way I could win in that ridiculous battle.

\N<Irime>To survive in the training corps filled with strong men, as
a powerless woman, I had to put in the maximum effort I
could muster.

\N<Segi>I understand your feelings... painfully well. As I've said
before... I feel the same way.

\N<Irime>It all started when I entered the competition in place of my
husband who was bedridden with illness. But... I can't bring
myself to resent him.

\N<Irime>If my husband had been healthy and had taken my place to
fight in the training corps for me and our daughter, I'm
sure he would have suffered too... you know.
\N<Segi>...
\N<Irime>But... even so, I've been feeling anxious lately.

\N<Irime>Segi, you've heard about it too, right? The secret potion
from the Lyuda people... Mind. Lyuda or whatever it's
called.

\N<Segi>...Yes. That medicine gives us powerless ones strength, but
at a cost...
\N<Irime>Right. Lately, I've started to feel its effects on my skin.

\N<Irime>...To survive in the training corps to protect my husband
and daughter. That's what I should have been struggling
for...

\N<Irime>When I'm held by that guy Zuuteruka, I feel like I could
forget even that. Surrendering everything to the pleasure
etched into my body, giving up... exposing myself.

\N<Irime>Heh... it's like I don't care anymore. Just enjoy this
moment, that's what I think.

\N<Irime>It feels like my heart and body are being remade to their
liking...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Irime>But if I truly drowned in pleasure and threw everything
away... it would surely bring suffering to my family.

\N<Irime>Heh... it's quite the joke, isn't it? To think that I slept
with a man I didn't even like in order to save my family,
and now it's all turned upside down...

\N<Irime>Segi... What about you? Can you still control your ego and
endure?

\N<Irime>As for me... I might be reaching my limit. With this
seemingly endless self-questioning... I have no idea how
much longer I can bear it...
\N<Segi>Ms. Irime...
